stories.storyText:
[Code Name] Ela
[Gender] Female
[Combat Experience] Undisclosed
[Place of Birth] Undisclosed
[Date of Birth] Nov 18
[Race] Undisclosed
[Height] 173cm
[Infection Status]
Medical tests have confirmed that no infection is present.

[Physical Strength] Normal
[Mobility] Standard
[Physical Resilience] Standard
[Tactical Acumen] Excellent
[Combat Skill] Excellent
[Originium Arts Assimilation] ■■

A member of Team Rainbow, Ela is independent, rebellious, adaptive, and a strong leader.
Her Grzmot mine is a powerful non-lethal weapon that disables the enemy through sound and shock.

Imaging tests reveal clear, normal outlines of internal organs, and no abnormal shadows have been detected. Originium granules have not been detected in the circulatory system and there is no sign of infection. At this time, this operator is believed to be uninfected.

[Cell-Originium Assimilation] 0%
Ela shows no sign of Originium infection.

[Blood Originium-Crystal Density] Undisclosed
The Medical Department has agreed not to disclose the relevant data.

Elżbieta 'Ela' Bosak is a member of Team Rainbow. She was involved in the Krysztauowa Incident and became an associate of Rhodes Island following the conclusion of that incident.
As leaders of their respective squads, Ela presents a very different first impression from the cautious and serious Ash.
Do not mistake her artistic energy and creativity for inexperience or incompetence, however. She is an outstanding combatant, with excellent leadership and decision-making skills.
It is worth mentioning that Team Rainbow members are only working with us temporarily. They are not formally employed by Rhodes Island, and with how much they have on their hands, it would not be advisable to call on their help too often.

Ela is the most independent and mercurial member of Team Rainbow that we have encountered.
She can pick up a spraypaint can and hang out with operators who hail from the streets, talk at length about advanced art theory, or hand a blanket to a patient sitting outside the Medical Department and strike up a conversation.
When the application of force is called for, she can deploy her Grzmot mine with great precision, or lead an elite squad to achieve its objectives.
The combination of art and military in her background may remind some of Leithanien casters, but she shares few other traits with them. It is hard to define her, and that's how she likes it.

Ela prefers to listen to other people's stories over telling her own. In this unfamiliar place, every story increases her understanding of the people and things around her.
With her own story, however, Ela is often evasive, except when talking of her grandfather, if an operator should ask about the old uniform she carries. Of her other family, Ela says little, except that her father is dead, and that she is not on good terms with her sister.
Although Ela's attitude is cold when she talks of her sister, she displays a little bit of pride when discussing how she has embarked on this unknown journey, while her sister has not. When asked how she would describe the experience to her sister, Ela paused, then said, 'Let's make sure I get to see her again first.'

Ela is skeptical of authority, and not afraid to butt heads with superiors over orders that seem unreasonable.
That does not mean she objects to everything indiscriminately, only that her ability, independent nature and strong will make her unwilling to accept an overbearing attitude from those who are less informed, something that is perhaps colored by her previous experiences. On the other hand, pairing Ela with good teammates and giving astute commands goes a long way toward avoiding conflict with her.
As a matter of fact, Ela has maintained a good relationship with Rhodes Island following an initial acclimation period, partly because Rhodes Island does not interfere with Team Rainbow's operations, and partly because Rhodes Island has demonstrated trustworthy competence, while also trusting Ela's decisions in the field.

[Classified Log]
Modification of the Grzmot mine's core components was not difficult, thanks to previous experience with the G52 Tactical Shield. While the two weapons disable enemies in different ways, it was not difficult to recreate the Grzmot's effect using Originium products
The sensor was the bigger issue, but not one that our Originium engineers couldn't handle. This old Caprinae even spent a whole lunchtime with Ela discussing whether to add new features to the Grzmot mine.
It was the adhesives that proved the most challenging. Ela was very particular about the feel, and we tried a lot of materials with little success, from the latest Columbian ones to traditional Sargonian crafts. It was Operator Vanilla who provided a breakthrough, as the Originium Slug that she keeps secretes a slime that can be processed to a satisfactory consistency.
After giving Vanilla a written guarantee, the Originium Slug now resides in a small pen in a corner of the workshop. Vanilla visits it every day, as does Tachanka when he is around. As a matter of fact, the Originium Slug has been fed so well that its slime production rate is beginning to outpace Grzmot mine production.

skins.description:
An outfit commonly worn by Operators.
While not as practical as a uniform, it's what they find most comfortable.

An outfit that has been improved after the Operator's Promotion.
Custom-made to suit each Operator's experiences and needs, these outfits are designed to provide them maximum flexibility on any battlefield. Furthermore, this is all done without compromising the comfort that they've come to expect.

<color name=#ffffff>Rainbow Six Collaborative Series/Safehouse. A set of clothes that Ela bought at the market. Light and comfortable, it is her favorite outfit in the safehouse. She particularly likes how the local hat looks on her.</color>

modules.desc:
Operator Ela has demonstrated a remarkable aptitude for battlefield ambush and trap deployment.
The Field Operations Department has thus passed the following resolution:
This operator shall be appointed a Specialist Operator during field operations. In witness whereof,
This badge is hereby conferred upon the above named, whether this band of soldiers needs such recognition notwithstanding.

One day... 'Myrinia was precisely in need of these medicines, Rhodes Island mercenary madam. You have our boundless thanks for coming all this way!' 'Elżbieta Bosak, operator codename Ela.' 'Hah! There was an old local saying before Sargon came: 'Respect the Minoan, even should they come bearing gifts.' You may be of Kazimierz, but that striking majesty—in you is the stuff of Minos!' 'I'm not sure that saying means what you think... Anyway, I'd like to ask you something, seeing as you're the leader around here.' 'Very well! As temple priest, I promise you that any answers I hold are yours!' 'I'm told this nation only recently gained independence?' 'Yes and no. Minos and Hymnoi were born to walk together, two peas in a pod, their histories as one; that said, speaking solely of when we drove out the Sargonians... Hah! The great River Delphi has seen neither pike nor polearm in decades! While West Vouivre still battles with Sargon...' 'And since your independence, you've been working on a large-scale cultural revival and art restoration?' '...Oh, so that's what you meant—I should be clear, placid as Myrinia is, it is by no means in dire straits. All the daily medicines and inhibitor doses used by the villagers are, as you can see, a duty easily borne by my temple. Let alone the claim that the sculptures outside—dating from the ancient city-states—are left unrepaired for a lack of funds!' 'Then why are you leaving your marble statues out there in pieces?' 'The course and prayers of our ceremonial rites, the neighbors and their village, all I know by heart; the bygone affairs of the three capitals, and the wider state of the greater land, I am likewise well-informed. 'Yet how can I possibly know the who, the what, and the why of those sculptures' makers and molders? Whither did strike their chisel, and whence did fall their hammer? 'I know not, the villagers know not, and nor do the masters of crafts or the sophists of the scholastic—how then, can I repair them? Hence, they have never been repaired.' 'Why not use your imagination?' 'Nay, nay! The chroniclers shall be anonymous, as shall the heroes! The man in the wine jar with not a coming nor a going has biographers still to testify of him to this very day. 'Think about it, now. Supposing today I went to the wilds beyond the village and sought a statue, unknown and unnamed. Presumably by my Forte's strength, I could on my own have it standing anew. 'Yet I could also go out today and plant a stake in the ground, and what difference would that make?' '...When the artist is known by no one, the art transcends society.' 'If you were to put it in baffling terms, then more or less, yes!' 'But it's not like you want art that transcends society.' '...If you were to put it in baffling terms, then more or less, yes!' 'Then how about art that records society?' Another day... The fowls commence their recital of the verse of daybreak, Minos's golden sun dawns His golden gift upon the village of Myrinia as He always has, and the villagers are startled to find that the temple's solemn walls do not, as was their custom and theirs alone, return that gift with the purest white dazzling gleam. 'Priest, what are these garish drawings?' 'The artist claims them to be our very selves—this is a kind of foreign wall art by the name of 'graffiti'!'

voice_lines.voiceText: Since you're stuck here sifting through documents, I might as well help you solve a few problems around the office.
Hitting supply lines does a whole lot more damage than taking out people.
If you ask me, your office is on the bland side. Just hit me up if you ever want to mix things up a little.
The whole 'cozy family relationship' thing isn't for me.
I get a lot more out of talking to strangers than I do from that 'self-help' shtick.
We define ourselves by symbols, but those symbols can be perverted. Reused. Reworked, reframed, remade. In a word, stolen. Who are you then?
I don't mind helping you run errands out of combat, but on the battlefield, I need ample room to call the shots.
When someone can't find fault with your results and has to resort to nitpicking your attitude, that tells you everything you need to know about them.
To call the shots, you need to prove that you've got what it takes – and you've certainly done that. So, where are you sending me next?
Your workload is clearly excessive, even by the highest standards. Take a rest.
Codename Ela, member of Team Rainbow. Just give me my objective, then sit back and wait for the good news.
Picked up a few new tricks.
A medal? Thanks. Workmanship's not bad at all, as far as decorations go.
Together, we can shake the very stars from the sky.
At least make it challenging.
Time to show you what I can do.
No time to waste.
I'll make you regret this.
A tooth for a tooth.
An eye for an eye.
I got this.
Idziemy.
Here's a memento.
That will slow them down.
Eat this!
Don't move!
The end justifies the means.
I'm sorry, was I too fast for you?
That's it?
Try to keep up!
This place isn't half bad.
Do me a favor, don't talk to me.
Tell me YOUR story.
Arknights.
Happy New Year. I'm ready to face even more challenges.
I'm here.
You've been haunted by all sorts of unreasonableness, ever since the day you were born. You have no choice but to fight back.
Rhodes Island is an incredibly inclusive place – and that's a big deal.
